@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Our History";
}

<section class="page-hero">
    <h1 class="display-5">Our History</h1>
    <p class="hero-lead">Three generations at the same address — and a promise never to hurry a reader.</p>
</section>

<div class="content-section">
    <div class="row g-5">
        <div class="col-lg-7">
            <h3>The house of Harrington</h3>
            <p>
                In the winter of 1892, Edmund Harrington opened a modest bindery above a chemist’s shop,
                repairing folios brought in by professors and collectors. Patrons lingered; they spoke of books
                they wished to find. Within a decade, the shelves had multiplied, and the bindery had become
                a bookseller’s proper room.
            </p>
            <p>
                We have never aspired to be the largest shop — only the most considered. Each volume is chosen
                by hand. We favour editions with integrity of paper and type, authors who reward patience,
                and works that belong in a library meant to outlast its owner.
            </p>

            <blockquote class="history-pullquote">
                “A bookshop should feel like a room one was always meant to enter.”
                <footer class="mt-2" style="font-size: 0.9rem; font-style: normal; color: var(--ink-muted);">— Margaret Harrington, 1968</footer>
            </blockquote>

            <h3>Today</h3>
            <p class="mb-0">
                The catalogue you browse is our continuing ledger — rare finds, restored classics, and new
                works we believe worthy of gilt and cloth. Whether you visit in person or reserve from afar,
                you are received as a guest of the house, not a transaction.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-5">
            <div class="contact-info-card h-100 d-flex flex-column justify-content-center text-center p-4">
                <p style="font-family: var(--font-caps); font-size: 0.65rem; letter-spacing: 0.2em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--gold); margin-bottom: 1rem;">Established</p>
                <p style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 3rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--ink); line-height: 1; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">1892</p>
                <p style="font-style: italic; color: var(--ink-muted); margin-bottom: 2rem;">Over a century at the trade</p>
                <hr style="border-color: var(--gold-pale); width: 40%; margin: 0 auto 2rem;" />
                <p style="font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--ink-soft); line-height: 1.7;">
                    Reading room open Tuesday through Saturday.<br />
                    Appointments welcomed for private viewings.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<section class="cta-banner mt-2">
    <h5>Questions of catalogue or condition?</h5>
    <p>Our desk is always attended during opening hours.</p>
    <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="Contact" class="btn btn-gold btn-lg">Write to us</a>
</section>
